	<fdd:identificationAndDescription>
		<fdd:fullName>Apple ProRes 422 LT</fdd:fullName>
		<fdd:keywords>
			<fdd:keyword>moving image, video formats</fdd:keyword>
			<fdd:keyword>codec formats</fdd:keyword>
			<fdd:keyword>compression formats</fdd:keyword>
		</fdd:keywords>
		<fdd:description>
			<p>Apple ProRes 422 LT is the third-highest data-rate version of the ProRes 422 codecs.  <a href="http://www.apple.com/final-cut-pro/docs/Apple_ProRes_White_Paper.pdf">Apple literature</a> highlights the value of Apple ProRes 422 LT as an editing codec, stating that it "is perfect for environments where storage capacity and data rate are at a premium."</p>
			<p>In order to compare the members of the ProRes 422 family, this Web site uses 10-bit picture data with an HD (1920x1080) frame size and a frame rate of 29.97 fps.  Uncompressed, this yields about 560 GB per hour. Although the variable bit rate for ProRes means that results will vary, specialists report that the 102 Mbps target data rate for Apple ProRes 422 would yield a one-hour file of about 45 GB.</p>
			<p>See the <fddLink id="fdd000389">Apple ProRes 422 Codec Family</fddLink> for a general description of the shared technical characteristics as well as history of the format.</p>
		</fdd:description>
		<fdd:shortDescription>Apple ProRes 422 LT, one of the more highly compressed Apple ProRes 422 codecs, is primarily geared for projects when digital storage space and data rate are limited. </fdd:shortDescription>
		<fdd:productionPhase>Production (initial state) and post production (middle state).</fdd:productionPhase>
